# MCP Server Environment Variables Template
# Copy to .env and fill in your actual values
# NEVER commit .env with real keys to version control

# ==============================================================================
# Qdrant Vector Store (REQUIRED for qdrant-docs MCP server)
# ==============================================================================
# Get your Qdrant credentials at: https://cloud.qdrant.io/
QDRANT_API_URL=https://your-qdrant-instance.cloud.qdrant.io:6333
QDRANT_API_KEY=your-qdrant-api-key-here

# ==============================================================================
# OpenAI (REQUIRED for embeddings in qdrant-docs)
# ==============================================================================
# Get your OpenAI API key at: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# Used for: text-embedding-3-small model in qdrant-docs semantic search
OPENAI_API_KEY=your-openai-api-key-here
MODEL_NAME=gpt-4o-mini

# ==============================================================================
# Context7 (OPTIONAL - provides higher rate limits for Context7 MCP server)
# ==============================================================================
# Get your Context7 API key at: https://context7.com/dashboard
# Benefits:
#   - Higher rate limits for documentation queries
#   - Access to private repositories (if configured)
#   - Better performance under load
#
# Note: Context7 works without an API key but with lower rate limits
#
# IMPORTANT: Use CONTEXT7_API_KEY (NOT CALCOM_API_KEY)
# CALCOM_API_KEY was a bug that has been fixed
CONTEXT7_API_KEY=your-context7-api-key-here

# ==============================================================================
# Setup Instructions
# ==============================================================================
# 1. Copy this file to .env:
#    cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Fill in your actual API keys in .env
#
# 3. Add to your shell environment (~/.bashrc or ~/.zshrc):
#    export QDRANT_API_URL="your-value"
#    export QDRANT_API_KEY="your-value"
#    export OPENAI_API_KEY="your-value"
#    export CONTEXT7_API_KEY="your-value"
#
# 4. Reload your shell:
#    source ~/.bashrc  # or source ~/.zshrc
#
# 5. Verify environment variables are set:
#    echo "QDRANT_API_URL: ${QDRANT_API_URL:+SET}"
#    echo "QDRANT_API_KEY: ${QDRANT_API_KEY:+SET}"
#    echo "OPENAI_API_KEY: ${OPENAI_API_KEY:+SET}"
#    echo "CONTEXT7_API_KEY: ${CONTEXT7_API_KEY:+SET}"
#
# ==============================================================================
# Security Best Practices
# ==============================================================================
# ✅ DO:
#   - Store secrets in shell environment
#   - Use .env for local development only
#   - Add .env to .gitignore
#   - Keep .env.example updated (without real values)
#   - Use ${VAR} syntax in MCP configs
#
# ❌ DON'T:
#   - Commit .env files with real keys
#   - Hardcode keys in config files
#   - Share API keys in screenshots
#   - Use ${env:VAR} syntax (incorrect)
#
# ==============================================================================
# Cost Monitoring
# ==============================================================================
# OpenAI (text-embedding-3-small):
#   - Monitor at: https://platform.openai.com/usage
#   - Used only for qdrant-docs semantic search
#   - Cost: ~$0.02 per 1M tokens (very cheap)
#
# Qdrant:
#   - Monitor at: https://cloud.qdrant.io/
#   - Free tier available
#   - Check collection size and query volume
#
# Context7:
#   - Monitor at: https://context7.com/dashboard
#   - Free tier available
#   - Upgrade if hitting rate limits
#
# ==============================================================================
# Troubleshooting
# ==============================================================================
# If you see authentication errors:
#   1. Verify env vars are set: echo $VAR_NAME
#   2. Check .env file has correct values
#   3. Ensure shell environment is loaded
#   4. Restart Claude Code after changing env vars
#
# If Context7 returns 401 errors:
#   1. Verify using CONTEXT7_API_KEY (not CALCOM_API_KEY)
#   2. Check key validity at: https://context7.com/dashboard
#   3. Regenerate key if needed
#
# ==============================================================================
# Additional Notes
# ==============================================================================
# - This template reflects the state after the 2025-11-30 MCP migration
# - All MCP servers are now configured at user (global) scope
# - Environment variables must be accessible globally (in shell)
# - For detailed setup guide, see: MCP-SETUP.md
